1291B 101st Legislative Session 1291
2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1291
AMENDME NT 1291B
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Gosch
This bill has been extensively amended (hoghoused) and may no longer be consistent with the original
intention of the sponsor.
1 An Act to amend the process for calculating permit a school district's general fund
2 base percentage participation in the property and casualty captive insurance
3 company fund.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
5 Section 1. That § 5-14-39 be AMENDED:
6 5-14-39. There is hereby established in the state treasury the property and
7 casualty captive insurance company fund. The Bureau of Human Resources and
8 Administration may enter into an agreement with a captive insurance company for the
9 management of the company's funds. Money in this fund may be used to pay for property
10 and casualty losses for state owned state-owned property or property leased or owned by
11 a school district, as well as administrative and reinsurance costs for this fund.
12 Interest earned on money in the fund shall must be deposited into the fund.
13 Unexpended money and any interest that may be credited to the fund shall must remain
14 in the fund. Any money in the property and casualty captive insurance company fund is
15 continuously appropriated. Any money deposited into and distributed from the fund shall
16 must be set forth in an informational budget, as described in § 4-7-7.2.
17 The Bureau of Human Resources and Administration may enter into an agreement
18 with a captive insurance company for purposes of this section.
19 Section 2. This Act is effective beginning July 1, 2027.
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

